From 23706a049e9930115f91b9387bb680243307e51d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mpl_risk <dev@example.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 22:17:02 -1000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] feat: configurable model URL and IndexedDB calibration
 persistence

Two changes, both backwards compatible.

1. BlazeGaze.loadModel() takes an optional modelUrl. It previously hardcoded
   ${self.location.origin}/web/model.json, which forces any host application
   that serves static files under a different prefix to proxy that one path.

2. adapt() personalises the model weights in place, and those weights live in
   the Web Worker. Because a full page navigation destroys the worker, a
   calibration performed on one page cannot affect the next. Add
   saveCalibration(key) / loadModel(url, key), which persist and restore the
   personalised model via tf.js's indexeddb:// IO handler. IndexedDB is
   available in a WorkerGlobalScope, and tf.js registers the handler there
   (IS_BROWSER is true when WorkerGlobalScope is defined).

Without a calibrationKey the behaviour is exactly as before.
